dtable on climate change of the earth institute at columbia university with his experiences both in us and china he has been actively involved in the us china collaboration on energy and climate change mr he received an ma from columbia university on climate and society bs from peking university on geography and he is currently doing a phd in the energy and resources group at uc berkeley publications the 5 most recent are displayed more publications esi bulletin the real drivers of carbon capture and storage in china richard k morse varun rai gang he esi bulletin vol 3 2010 pdf+ cover remaking the world's largest coal market the quest to develop large coal power bases in china dr huaichuan rui richard k morse gang he program on energy and sustainable development 2010 pdf+ cover the world's greatest coal arbitrage china's coal import behavior and implications for the global coal market richard k morse gang he program on energy and sustainable development 2010 pdf+ cover overcoming imperfections richard k morse gang he trading carbon magazine 2010 html+ pdf+ cover making carbon offsets work in the developing world lessons from the chinese wind controversy gang he richard k morse program on energy and sustainable development working paper 90 2010 pdf+ events & presentations the 5 most recent are displayed more events & presentations prospects and bottlenecks for clean energy cooperation october 25 2010 seminar gang he pdf+ presentation available china scope at mit understanding china's economy and society september 18 2010 workshop gang he pdf+ presentation available research experience in carbon sequestration 2010 july 27 2010 workshop gang he pdf+ ppt+ presentation conference agenda available the china factor short and long term drivers of chinese coal imports june 29 2010 research in progress seminar gang he richard k morse guest lecture china's coal and power conflict and its broad impacts january 28 2010 lecture gang he search people everything recent commentary p